This paper is about mining user-centered concepts from web documents and queries, which is a core research problem in text understanding. The paper discusses techniques for tagging documents with user-centered concepts and constructing a topic-concept-instance taxonomy, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also mentions offline evaluation and online A/B testing, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses how the system has improved search and news feeds recommendation, which is relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
